<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="580" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1663,1798]" pageId="2" pageNumber="580">
Known from 
<collectingCountry box="[305,393,1663,1689]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="580">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Central and South America, and the Lesser Antilles, 90 species have been identified in the Neotropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R." box="[291,587,1699,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="580" pagination="1 - 566" refId="ref5887" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R. (2017) Catalog of the Neotropical Trichoptera (Caddisflies). Zookeys, 654, 1 - 566. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 654.9516" type="journal article" year="2017">Holzenthal &amp; Calor 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Blahnik, R. J. &amp; Armitage, B. J." box="[601,905,1699,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="580" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref5021" refString="Blahnik, R. J. &amp; Armitage, B. J. (2019) The Trichoptera of Panama. XII. Contributions to the family Glossosomatidae (Insecta: Trichoptera) in Panama. Insecta Mundi, 0710, 1 - 17." type="book chapter" year="2019">Blahnik &amp; Armitage 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Additional taxa are found in North America. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,240,1736,1762]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="580">Panama</collectingCountry>
is home to 13 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Armitage, B. J. &amp; Harris, S. C. &amp; Arefina-Armitage, T. I. &amp; Cornejo, A." box="[503,741,1735,1762]" pageId="2" pageNumber="580" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref4687" refString="Armitage, B. J., Harris, S. C., Arefina-Armitage, T. I. &amp; Cornejo, A. (2015) The Trichoptera of Panama. III. Updated species list for caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) in the Republic of Panama. Insecta Mundi, 0442, 1 - 16." type="book chapter" year="2015">
Armitage 
<emphasis box="[618,668,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="580">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Blahnik, R. J. &amp; Armitage, B. J." box="[753,1051,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="580" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref5021" refString="Blahnik, R. J. &amp; Armitage, B. J. (2019) The Trichoptera of Panama. XII. Contributions to the family Glossosomatidae (Insecta: Trichoptera) in Panama. Insecta Mundi, 0710, 1 - 17." type="book chapter" year="2019">Blahnik &amp; Armitage 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Herein we add two more species from western 
<collectingCountry box="[307,399,1772,1798]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="580">Panama</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
